{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Luk|17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","chapter":17,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":1,"text":"He said to his disciples, “Offenses will certainly come, but woe to the one through whom they come!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":2,"text":"It would be better for him if a millstone were hung around his neck and he were thrown into the sea than for him to cause one of these little ones to stumble.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":3,"text":"Be on your guard. If your brother sins, rebuke him, and if he repents, forgive him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":4,"text":"And if he sins against you seven times in a day, and comes back to you seven times, saying, ‘I repent,’ you must forgive him.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":5,"text":"The apostles said to the Lord, “Increase our faith.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":6,"text":"“If you have faith the size of a mustard seed,” the Lord said, “you can say to this mulberry tree, ‘Be uprooted and planted in the sea,’ and it will obey you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":7,"text":"“Which one of you having a servant tending sheep or plowing will say to him when he comes in from the field, ‘Come at once and sit down to eat’?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":8,"text":"Instead, will he not tell him, ‘Prepare something for me to eat, get ready, and serve me while I eat and drink; later you can eat and drink’?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":9,"text":"Does he thank that servant because he did what was commanded?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":10,"text":"In the same way, when you have done all that you were commanded, you should say, ‘We are unworthy servants; we’ve only done our duty.’”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":11,"text":"While traveling to Jerusalem, he passed between Samaria and Galilee.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":12,"text":"As he entered a village, ten men with leprosy met him. They stood at a distance","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":13,"text":"and raised their voices, saying, “Jesus, Master, have mercy on us!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":14,"text":"When he saw them, he told them, “Go and show yourselves to the priests.” And while they were going, they were cleansed.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":15,"text":"But one of them, seeing that he was healed, returned and, with a loud voice, gave glory to God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":16,"text":"He fell facedown at his feet, thanking him. And he was a Samaritan.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":17,"text":"Then Jesus said, “Were not ten cleansed? Where are the nine?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":18,"text":"Didn’t any return to give glory to God except this foreigner?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":19,"text":"And he told him, “Get up and go on your way. Your faith has saved you.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":20,"text":"When he was asked by the Pharisees when the kingdom of God would come, he answered them, “The kingdom of God is not coming with something observable;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":21,"text":"no one will say, ‘See here!’ or ‘There!’ For you see, the kingdom of God is in your midst.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":22,"text":"Then he told the disciples, “The days are coming when you will long to see one of the days of the Son of Man, but you won’t see it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":23,"text":"They will say to you, ‘See there!’ or ‘See here!’ Don’t follow or run after them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":24,"text":"For as the lightning flashes from horizon to horizon and lights up the sky, so the Son of Man will be in his day.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":25,"text":"But first it is necessary that he suffer many things and be rejected by this generation.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":26,"text":"“Just as it was in the days of Noah, so it will be in the days of the Son of Man:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":27,"text":"People went on eating, drinking, marrying and being given in marriage until the day Noah boarded the ark, and the flood came and destroyed them all.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":28,"text":"It will be the same as it was in the days of Lot: People went on eating, drinking, buying, selling, planting, building.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":29,"text":"But on the day Lot left Sodom, fire and sulfur rained from heaven and destroyed them all.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":30,"text":"It will be like that on the day the Son of Man is revealed.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:31","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":31,"text":"On that day, a man on the housetop, whose belongings are in the house, must not come down to get them. Likewise the man who is in the field must not turn back.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:32","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":32,"text":"Remember Lot’s wife!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:33","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":33,"text":"Whoever tries to make his life secure will lose it, and whoever loses his life will preserve it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:34","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":34,"text":"I tell you, on that night two will be in one bed; one will be taken and the other will be left.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:35","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":35,"text":"Two women will be grinding grain together; one will be taken and the other left.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:37","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","bookOrder":41,"chapter":17,"verse":37,"text":"“Where, Lord?” they asked him. He said to them, “Where the corpse is, there also the vultures will be gathered.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Luk","chapter":17,"paragraphStarts":[1,5,6,7,11,14,15,17,20,22,26,37],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Warnings from Jesus"},{"beforeVerse":5,"text":"Faith and Duty"},{"beforeVerse":11,"text":"Ten Men Healed"},{"beforeVerse":20,"text":"The Coming of the Kingdom"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 18:6–7","book":"Mat","chapter":18,"verse":6,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 9:42","book":"Mrk","chapter":9,"verse":42,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 11:19","book":"1Co","chapter":11,"verse":19,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" said to his disciples, “Offenses will certainly come,"},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit “It is impossible for offenses not to come"},{"kind":"text","text":" but woe"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 22:22","book":"Luk","chapter":22,"verse":22,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" to the one through whom they come!"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 13:41","book":"Mat","chapter":13,"verse":41,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 18:6–7","book":"Mat","chapter":18,"verse":6},{"label":"Mk 9:42","book":"Mrk","chapter":9,"verse":42},{"label":"1Co 11:19","book":"1Co","chapter":11,"verse":19},{"label":"Lk 22:22","book":"Luk","chapter":22,"verse":22},{"label":"Mt 13:41","book":"Mat","chapter":13,"verse":41}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit “It is impossible for offenses not to come"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"It would be better for him if a millstone were hung around his neck and he were thrown into the sea than for him to cause one of these little ones to stumble."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 8:9","book":"1Co","chapter":8,"verse":9,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Co 8:9","book":"1Co","chapter":8,"verse":9}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Be"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 18:15","book":"Mat","chapter":18,"verse":15,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 18:21","book":"Mat","chapter":18,"verse":21,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" on your guard. If your brother sins,"},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Other mss add against you"},{"kind":"text","text":" rebuke"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lv 19:17","book":"Lev","chapter":19,"verse":17,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" him, and if he repents, forgive"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 6:14","book":"Mat","chapter":6,"verse":14,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" him. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 18:15","book":"Mat","chapter":18,"verse":15},{"label":"Mt 18:21","book":"Mat","chapter":18,"verse":21},{"label":"Lv 19:17","book":"Lev","chapter":19,"verse":17},{"label":"Mt 6:14","book":"Mat","chapter":6,"verse":14}],"footnotes":[{"marker":2,"text":"Other mss add against you"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"And if he sins against you seven times in a day, and comes back to you seven times, saying, ‘I repent,’ you must forgive him.”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Luk:17:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 17:19–20","book":"Mat","chapter":17,"verse":19,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 9:28–29","book":"Mrk","chapter":9,"verse":28,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" apostles "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 6:13","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":13,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" said to the Lord, “Increase our faith.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 9:24","book":"Mrk","chapter":9,"verse":24,"letter":"d"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 17:19–20","book":"Mat","chapter":17,"verse":19},{"label":"Mk 9:28–29","book":"Mrk","chapter":9,"ve